### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When using `"aot": true` in the test config if a CLI app (as introduced in v20), a component test that uses `RouterTestingHarness` and `TestBed.overrideComponent` will fail, whereas it works in JiT.

Consider the following routed component that uses an `Alert` component and the `FormGroupDirective` from `ReactiveFormsModule`.

```html
<app-alert></app-alert>
<h1>User</h1>
<form [formGroup]="userForm"></form>
```

```ts
import { Component, inject } from '@angular/core';
import { NonNullableFormBuilder, ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { Alert } from '../alert/alert';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-user',
  imports: [ReactiveFormsModule, Alert],
  templateUrl: './user.html',
  styleUrl: './user.css',
})
export class User {
  userForm = inject(NonNullableFormBuilder).group({});
}
```

The following tests both succeed in JiT (one using `TestBed.createComponent` and the other using `RouterTestingHarness.create`:

```ts
import { TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing';

import { User } from './user';
import { Alert } from '../alert/alert';
import { provideRouter } from '@angular/router';
import { RouterTestingHarness } from '@angular/router/testing';

describe('User', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    TestBed.overrideComponent(User, {
      remove: {
        imports: [Alert],
      },
      add: {
        imports: [Alert], // override with itself for the repro but fails with a real stub as well
      },
    });
    TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      providers: [provideRouter([{ path: 'user', component: User }])],
    });
  });

  it('should display a user with RouterTestingHarness.create', async () => {
    const harness = await RouterTestingHarness.create('/user');
    const element = harness.routeNativeElement!;
    expect(element.querySelector('h1')?.textContent).toContain('User');
  });

  it('should display a user with TestBed.createComponent', () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(User);
    const element = fixture.nativeElement as HTMLElement;
    expect(element.querySelector('h1')?.textContent).toContain('User');
  });
});
```

Flipping the AoT switch in `angular.json` makes the `RouterTestingHarness` test fail with the error below,
